Text.Value: Leave.
The Guild ain't gone, for what it's worth. If I know the boss, well... we're just restructuring.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild)

Text.Value: Don't give me that squinty side-eye like all these paranoid Guildies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Friendly, amused at the suspicion you're receiving around here. You're a mercenary company, but you are here to help.

Text.Value: Far as I'm concerned, the deal you made with the boss holds. 'Til I hear otherwise, anyway.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - NO WINNER (delete if NPC is Zhent or Guild)

Text.Value: Look at you! There was mention of a shipment on the way.
I meant it when I said I respected Keene. I don't have to like my orders, just follow 'em.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild)

Text.Value: Leave.
Well, you can't be Zhentarim, mate - because Zhentarim don't go poking around in their cargo.
True, we've been better-liked in towns we bloody conquered - but it's hard to blame Nine-Fingers.
Leave.
No, mate. That can't be right. See - no one would be dumb enough to open Zhentarim cargo.
On top, undisputed, for years. Then you have to call the likes of us in to protect you from some shithead calling himself 'Stone Lord'. I'd be embarrassed, too.
I don't fancy reporting a botched shipment - and I doubt you fancy dying on the rack. So... what shipment?

EditorData.NodeContext: Playing dumb, cutting off the conversation - urging us to do the same.

Text.Value: I have business with the Zhentarim.
This cargo is yours.
Well. Made something of a mess, didn't we? My crew and I won't stop you tidying it up - not 'til we get some fresh orders from headquarters.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - NO WINNER (delete if NPC is Zhent or Guild)

Text.Value: Consider me an honorary Zhentarim. I was given this package to deliver.
Guild roof, Guild rules. I'll make sure my people know that.
The Black Network cares. Just so happens that we charge, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere, as if repeating a company motto she actually believes. Second line is her own addtion.

Text.Value: Whatever the Zhentarim's business with Nine-Fingers, I have my own to conduct.
That so? Go on, then - entertain me. The Guildhall isn't much fun these days.
Consider me an honorary Zhentarim. I was given this package to deliver.
The ones who were supposed to carry this are already dead. Better you don't ask - new Zhentarim leadership in the city.
Missed the welcome parade, did you? Hugging, tears - it was just lovely.
But your deal was with the Zhentarim themselves - and you delivered. Here - I hope it's generous enough. We've just landed a Guild contract, after all.

EditorData.NodeContext: easy-going, friendly - despite having just related the horrible fates of the OTHER Zhent we were dealing with,

Text.Value: Nine-Fingers is well-respected in the Zhentarim. If the Stone Lord's pressing in on her territory, we're here to help.
This cargo is yours.
Get used to us. I hear Nine-Fingers' hunt is not going well - she needs us now more than ever.
How does the Guild feel about you pressing in on their territory?

Synopsis: Zhent Mercenary informs player they are at the guild to help Nine-fingers beat the Stone Lord
